SFT FOOTBALL TRAVELS TO BURLINGTON tonight for a 7pm showdown with the Wildcats.
It has been a BIG week of SFT football!!
MONDAY, the JV beat Prairie View 20-0, while the Freshman lost a close 8-12 game to Mission Valley JV.
Thursday, the Freshman defeated Prairie View 50-18.
The 7th Grade shut out Anderson County 36-0.
The 8th Grade also shut out Anderson County 22-0.
We hope to make a good week great tonight in Burlington!
GO TRAIL!!

post_text: Schedules are now available for students in grades six through eight! Simply log in to PowerSchool to view your student's daily class schedule. If you notice errors please reach out to Ms. Mead and Ms. Black on our student support staff via phone or email for support. We are all systems go for Monday, and we cannot wait to see our students! Students may arrive at school after 7:20 AM for breakfast or to wait, with classes starting promptly at 8:00 AM. Masks are required on our campus, including outdoor spaces if you cannot socially distance six feet from others. Students riding buses are required to wear masks, and other students should mask up when they exit the vehicle getting dropped off or when walkers get onto the school grounds. We will check the temperatures of everyone entering the building each day. Students should have all materials in their backpacks that they will carry from class to class, and may carry a clear water bottle throughout the day if they choose. We will see you Monday morning!

post_text:
SFTHS Allen County Students: Deadlines are here!
1. If you are taking an online class, payment is due now! They will start deactivating accounts today. You have two options for payment: a. Pay online through the ACC site b. Go to ACC in Burlingame and pay in person.
2. Students taking on ACC classes from SFT teachers, your final bill must be paid by September 1st. Failure to do so will result in you being dropped from the class with no re-enrollment this semester. How do you pay online? Go to www.allencc.edu then log into your myallen site. You will pay there. If you are not sure you have balance, please log on to your myallen account. The current balance is there.
3. If you have an online textbook, you will need to go to ACC in Burlingame to pick up your textbook. According to ACC, many of our students have not done this yet. 4. Textbooks for in-person classes at SFT will be delivered to SFT and handed out by your teacher on August 31st.

post_text:
To Preschool and Kindergarten Families:
Because your child's first 5 years of life are so important, we want to help you provide the best start for your child. You've been invited to participate in Ages & Stages Questionnaires, ASQ-3, and the ASQ SE-2, online screenings to help you keep track of your child's development. You will be asked to answer questions about some things your child can and cannot do. The questionnaires include questions about your child's communication, gross motor skills, fine motor skills, problem-solving ability, and personal and social skills.
To participate in this screening study, please access BOTH of the following URLs by typing them into your Internet Browser.
ASQ-3 https://www.asqonline.com/family/0aea3d
ASQ SE-2 https://www.asqonline.com/family/305758
Please complete both of these screenings prior to Sept 20, 2020. Please feel free to let us know if you have any questions.
We look forward to your participation in ASQ-3 and ASQ SE-2!

Trail volleyball is recharged and ready to kick-off the 2020 season! Athletes in grades 7-12 came together the last three mornings and united as one. We broke down fundamentals, scrimmaged, played Queen of Courts (their favorite), and most importantly: cheered each other on and focused on team building. Practices for high school will begin next Tue/Wed 8:30-10am and scrimmages Wednesday evenings at 6-8:30pm. If you’ve attended ten conditioning sessions, we want you there! Full details on the http://trailvolleyball.com website.

post_text:
To: The Class of 2020
From: Mr. Graham and Mr. Erickson

We would like to recognize the seniors for their post-secondary plans. In year’s past, we would have a senior wear a t-shirt or some type of item showing where they were going. We would take the picture in the office and then post the information. This would include attending college, enlisting in the military, or joining the job force.

Here is what we are need from you:
1. A picture of you
2. A sentence or two saying what your plans are after high school.

We will post this on the school’s Facebook and Twitter pages. The feedback from community members has been positive in the past so please take the time to do this for them. They are proud of you and your accomplishments.

Please send the information to the both of us: pgraham@usd434.us and rerickson@usd434.us.

Thank you in advance.

HS Graduation for the Class of 2020:

At this time, Santa Fe Trail High School does not have a date set for the Class of 2020 graduation. We'd love too but at this time, there are too many "ifs."
The Governor's extension of the Stay at Home Order didn't help in the decision making.
We'd love to do something for our students. We know we can get organized quickly and pull something off with short notice. However, until we get more information from the county health department and Governor Kelly, we are just going to wait and see.

3. Click on Application for Admission
4. Click here to start....

This should get you to an 8-page document where you need to answer questions.

Once you have been admitted to ACC, when the all-clear is given, we can schedule the Accuplacer Test for admittance into math, science, and English classes through ACC.

Step 1 is to apply to the college.

If you have questions, please reach out to Mr. Graham at pgraham@usd434.us.

8th grade parents -- Mark your calendars!

Enrollment for 8th grade students will be held at Santa Fe Trail High School on Tuesday, March 17, and Thursday, March 19. Parents/Guardians and 8th grade students are invited to attend ONE of the sessions offered, which will provide information on high school transition and enrollment. Staff will be there to address individual questions and concerns. There will be optional school tours offered beginning at 6:30 in the Commons. An informational presentation will be held at 7:00 pm in the Auditorium. And, enrollment conferences will be conducted directly following the presentation in the Commons. This is where students will choose the classes they will take their freshman year.

SFT’s Early Childhood Screenings are coming up!
These screenings are the first step in getting signed up for preschool next year and are open to children from birth through age 5. All areas of development, including vision and hearing are checked. If your child already attends preschool at SAC, they do not need to come to a screening. Parents are highly encouraged to bring their child to a screening if they are not currently attending the preschool but plan on them starting in August. Please spread the word to families with preschool aged children in our district!

post_text:
For those Santa Fe Trail High School students interested in the ACT test, here are some calendar dates to take note of:

1. The deadline to register for the Saturday, February 8th, 2020 ACT test is Friday, January 10th, 2020. Please do this at act.org. You will have to pay for this test.

2. SFTHS plans to host on Wednesday, February 5th during the school day a PowerPrep ACT Test Prep session. Results from this prep have been beneficial to our students.

3. Then, on Tuesday, February 25th, students at SFTHS will have the opportunity to take a free ACT test provided by the State of Kansas. This will happen during the school day at SFT.

The hope is that students will do the Prep on February 5th, test on February 8th, have a chance for reflection, then retest on February 19th. It all a small window but we believe will be successful for our students. We tried this last year but a snow day ruined the second testing opportunity. It got pushed to April by the state.

The deadline for membership for the SFT Trap Shooting Team is Monday, January 20th, 2020. This is open to students in 7th – 12th grades. Reminder that either an Approved Firearms Certification or Hunters Safety Certificate is a league requirement. If you do not have either one of the certificates by April 11th, 2020 you will not be able to participate per league policy. If you need assistance obtaining a certificate please contact us, we would be glad to help. We plan to begin practicing the week of March 29th, 2020. We currently have participants that have made a commitment to the team, but still have plenty of room for more, so please contact us so we can have the roster complete by the 20th.

Depending on the amount of donations and fundraising, the fee to participate may vary. Fundraising options are in place to reduce or eliminate fees. If you have questions regarding fees, please contact us.

Contact information:

Wade Hoss: 785-220-6530 or hosswade@yahoo.com
Tanner Black: 785-230-1089 or tannerblack@yahoo.com
Dustin Garrison: 785-220-3578 or kssongdog@icloud.com
